In this press briefing, White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs provides updates on the President's schedule for the upcoming week, including signing the Family Smoking Prevention and Tobacco Control Act, meeting with the President of Chile, and hosting a town hall meeting on healthcare. He also discusses the House resolution on Iran and the President's stance on violence and condemnation. Additionally, Gibbs addresses questions on the indictment of Allen Stanford, the independence of the inspector general, the President's views on the healthcare cost, Iran, and the apology for slavery. He also mentions the upcoming trip to Russia and the President's preparations for it.